OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772679804
OL,3,CMichael Morpurgo says children learn
OL,4,Cbest by getting lost in a story
OL,6,FHe said: "As a teacher and a writer, I
OL,7,Fdon't think there's any better way for
OL,8,Fa child to learn for knowledge and for
OL,9,Finspiration and encouragement than
OL,10,Flosing yourself in a story, and you
OL,11,Fcan't do it quickly.
OL,13,F"Reading those stories when they're
OL,14,Fvery, very young, as young as
OL,15,Fpossible, that's the best way to sow
OL,16,Fthe seed.
OL,18,F"The next way to grow the plant is
OL,19,Fschool, and that is a teacher.
OL,26,@nD@JOUuD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772679804
OL,3,CMichael Morpurgo says children learn
OL,4,Cbest by getting lost in a story
OL,6,F"So if the teacher has the enthusiasm
OL,7,Fand the parent has the enthusiasm,
OL,8,Fthen we will get children reading
OL,9,Fagain.
OL,11,F"I don't think it's any good blaming
OL,12,Fphones or blaming iPads.
OL,14,F"They're a fact of life.
OL,16,F"There's a lot that's wonderful about
OL,17,Fthem and there's a lot that isn't.
OL,19,F"What's really important is that they
OL,20,Fdon't miss out on reading."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUvD@AOUxD@AOU{D@AOU|D@[O]
